arXiv.title:
$K^{+}ightarrow \mu^{+}
u_{\mu} 
u  ar 
u$ and $K^{+}ightarrow e^{+}
u_{e} 
u  ar 
u$ decays within the Chiral Perturbation Theory

arXiv.abstract:
Decays $K^{+} ightarrow \mu^{+}
u_{\mu} 
u  ar 
u$ and $K^{+}ightarrow e^{+}
u_{e} 
u  ar 
u$ are examined to the leading order in momenta in the framework of Chiral Perturbation Theory. Predictions of the Standard Model for the muon and electron differential energy spectra and branching ratios of $K_{\mu 3 
u}$ and $K_{e 3 
u}$ are presented.

arXiv.comments:
Talk presented by H. Toki at the Int. Conf. ``CONFINEMENT95'', March
  22-24, 1995, Osaka, Japan, 8 pages, latex, ( 3 figures - available on request
  from ssasaki@miho.rcnp.osaka-u.ac.jp )

arXiv.abstract:
Applications of QCD sum rules to exclusive decays of heavy mesons are reviewed. In detail, we discuss the calculations of the B and $D$ decay constants, the heavy-to-light form factors $f^+(p^2)$ and $f^0(p^2)$, and the strong couplings $g_{B^*B\pi}$ and $g_{D^*D\pi}$. Predictions are presented for the semileptonic weak decays $B 	o \pi  ar{l} 
u_l$ and $B 	o ho  ar{l} 
u_l$, and used to extract $V_{ub}$ from the measured decay widths. Results are also shown on $D 	o \pi  ar{l} 
u_l$ and $D^* 	o D \pi$. Furthermore, we reconsider the factorization hypothesis in nonleptonic two-body decays, and describe a sum rule estimate of the nonfactorizable contribution to the amplitude of $B 	o J/\psi K$.
